Nov 20 2009 	Totally surprised by how great this hotel was	Went to Vegas for a long weekend for an event at MGM, wanted a great deal and found it at Hard Rock. I wasn't expecting much for the cheap price and I was shocked by how much I loved the hotel. The room was a standard room and it was clean, comfortable and huge. It was off the strip, but it was the closest hotel to the airport and no more than a $10 cab ride to most other hotels. We found ourselves hanging out in our casino the most because they played awesome music in the lobby and it was overall just a fun atmosphere. They have some great restaurants and a few cool shops (even a tattoo parlor) too. It's a small hotel, and I found it a great thing to not have to walk 20 minutes just to get to my room. It's loud and it's a pretty young crowd (20's and 30's) so if you're looking for a quiet, elegant hotel - this is NOT it - stay at the Venetian! If you're looking for a low key, fun, affordable, nice hotel - stay here. I will definitely stay here next time I go to Vegas.	
