Nov 11 2009 	Hidden Resort Fee ruined an otherwise great stay.	We stayed in the new Paradise Tower and had a great stay - beautiful room, very clean. Great service with the Valet, they were fantastic even when our plans kept changing and we were getting the car in and back out every 15 minutes.Love all the decor and the new wing is under construction with the coffee shop area, but it's going to be great when it's done.HOWEVER, when we checked out we were SHOCKED to see a charge of $7.84/day for a &quot;resort fee&quot;. I should have read TripAdvisor as this seems like a common issue but since we had stayed here before, I didn't even do my homework.The worst was that when I challenged the charge at check-out (the first time I was aware of it), the desk clerk told me that we were told upon sign-in (we weren't) and that we had signed off on the charge. She was very unpleasant and I asked for a manager . We waited for over 10 minutes and instead of a manager, she brought back a printout of what I supposedly signed.What had really happened was we checked in and they told us about the mini-bar and that our credit card would be charged for the remaining reservation days and then handed us an electronic signature pad, said &quot;ok, just hit 'accept' and sign and you'll be all set&quot;. We signed and didn't think anything of it.After the fact, we learned that the signature pad has several pages of &quot;terms&quot; that the desk clerks were just skipping over and then handing the signature pad to the guests.As we were continuing to argue with the desk clerk, two other people came in to check-in and beautifully, the desk clerks did the exact same thing to both of them - handing the signature pad to each gentleman with the &quot;just hit 'accept' and sign&quot; instructions and not mentioning the resort fee authorization. So, we pointed it out to them and neither of them were aware of any resort fee. We were worried about missing our flight, so we left with both gentleman arguing about the resort fee.When we returned home, we contacted the hotel management and they apologized and refunded the charges. They also indicated that they were going to address the problem.I truly hope they do because frankly, we got a great rate and if it had been $8/night more, we still would have stayed there. But it was the principle of the matter.I would still recommend the hotel but be sure to calculate an extra $8/day in your rate before booking and make sure to read the fine print when you check in. Trust, but verify!	
