Oct 27 2009 	Enjoyed it but there are hidden fees	October '09Overall had a good time but was disappointed with hidden costs and poor service.1) Internet service is not free. You have to pay a flat rate for each 24 hours of service. No mention of this on there website. Rate: $12.99 per day. 2)&quot;Resort Fee&quot; @ $7.84 per day--no big hardship but why hide it? Just another tax that I don't feel guests should have to pay. Apparently covers costs for pool maintenance, free shuttles etc. 3) I booked through a travel group, and prepaid, and was still billed over $700.00 for &quot;incidentals&quot; for a 5 night stay without being told. I can understand having to put down a reasonable deposit, but that's just wrong. (Received my credit about 3 days after checkout.) 4) If they are going to offer in-room snacks at ridiculously inflated prices they should be on top of things. I found some items in the snack tray had been consumed but resealed to look like they hadn't been touched. Reported it right away, so I wasn't billed for anything. Glad I checked. Too many of the staff are very cold and not very courteous. I had to deal with bad attitudes on several occasions--I get it, it's the Hard Rock, but you're not rock stars. I blame hotel management for this one. The pools are great, though some spots have very limited sun.The casino is relatively small but I can appreciate a space you won't get lost in. Cocktail waitresses don't always come around often enough and when you do order a drink they might keep you waiting longer than you'd like.Mr. Lucky's restaurant is reasonably priced and has decent food, but 3 out of the 4 times there, I had pretty bad service and or botched orders. Pink Taco has consistently great food and fair service but is a little more pricey than need be (Happy Hour is the best time for deals). Hard Rock Cafe has great food and I want to say good service ... Unfortunately, on one occassion, we received two checks for the same meal. To top it off, the second check was four times the actual cost of our meal! When we pointed this out to our waiter we were apologised to profusely and assured there would be no second charge. Of course, when the bank statement was checked a day or two later the second charge was there. We were back home by this time and could not complain in person. Needless to say my buddy was pretty livid. Note: There are a couple of reasonably priced restuarants just across the street from the hotel grounds you might want to try. You do have other options.So it's not perfect, but the good was good and the place does have a fun atmosphere. There are some some really great staff and they made up for some of the bad, but would I stay here again? Probably not. I would consider it if, say, one of my favorite acts were performing. I would recommend to a friend but only after all the warnings.	
