Sep 8 2009 	Outstanding	I stayed at the Hard Rock from Sept 4- Sept 7, aka Labor Day weekend. Before I went, I had read review upon review about how bad the customer service was, how noisy the hotel was, how it was overall a horribly overpriced hotel too far from the strip. i was nervous. I arrived at the hotel right around midnight on Friday night. They were out of the standard rooms - which was the room on my reservation- so they upgraded us, free of charge, to a brand-new, amazing suite for the night, with their apologies. The suite was beautiful, with 2 bathrooms, several flat screens &amp; mostly all white with a funky decor. I loved it. The next day we went back to check out of that little slice of heaven and again, I was nervous. i mean, hello - we had just spent the night in a deluxe suite, our room was bound to suck after that. We got our new room, which they had put us in the Paradise Tower on the 10th floor with a pool view. while it wasn't the suite, it was one of the nicest hotel rooms i had ever stayed in in Vegas. and all this after i had booked through a 3rd party site &amp; gotten the room for less than $90 a night. So room-wise, i was thrilled.Onto customer service. It was without a fault. From registration to the bell-hops to the staff at the restaurants to housekeeping, everyone was friendly, nice, helpful &amp; was always smiling. Reminder - i'm talking about labor day weekend here, people. the place was PACKED- but no one was ever rude or short with us. again, i was thrilled (and slightly shocked considering all the negatives i had read about on here).Is the hotel noisy? yes, of course. you're at the HARD ROCK. come on. they pump excellent rock music through the casino and the elevators and it's loud.but it's not deafening and frankly, i enjoyed it. it added to the atmosphere. our rooms- neither one- were noisy. i couldnt hear the people in the room next to us (as has been stated on this site). I couldnt hear the people at the pool - even at Rehab on Sunday. yes, i could hear the pool music, but just the beat - it wasnt loud enough to hear the words.yes - it is off the strip. but everyone who books a room there knows this. it's not like the hotel is keeping that a secret. sometimes it's nice to be off the strip &amp; the hotel has so much to do &amp; so many places to eat that i really didnt miss the strip this time.oh- and the spa is wonderful. steamroom, jacuzzi in the womens locker room &amp; full use of it for the day if you make a spa appointment is paradise.so, overall, i was more than pleased with my experience. the ONLY negative thing is the $150/night hold they put on a credit or debit card that is not released until you check out. that was dissapointing to me, but not enough of a dissapointment to ruin our trip.	
