ad very, very expensive drinks. The center bar in the main casino area was the place to be and the most fun was had there. This place is good for the young crowd that is interested in getting wasted and who don't care too much about their hotel room/amenities. Don't stay here if you are looking for luxury and impeccable service because you won't get it. All the employees are quite young and seem very immature at that. They seemed to lack proper training. They didn't even know how to say thank you. The Strip is quite far and you will spend a ton of $ on cab rides back and forth to the strip. There is no shuttle or at least there wasn't one 7 months ago. The icing on our stay here was being woken up at 6am both days with construction on our side of the building. We awoke to a crain outside our window and non stop beeping. It was unbelievable. AND they DO NOT tell you about this beforehand when making your reservation. Bottom line - if you go here BEWARE!!! I will never set foot in this place as long as I live.	
