Apr 17 2009 	Hard Rock Hotel is the Best Hotel In Vegas	We've been staying at the Hard Rock Hotel and it's still the best hotel in Vegas. We've stayed at the other bigger hotels in Vegas - but nothing compares to the Hard Rock. It's Classy, full of great amentities, friendly, and reasonbly priced.It offers something for everyone. Of course it's geared towards the younger, hip crowd. But there is something here for everyone from 80 to 2. The pool is the best and unique. The restaurants and bar or fabulous (check out the new Rare 120). Starbucks just a quick elevator ride down from your room.The gaming area is intimate and fun. The staff was fabulous - better than ever. We rquested assistance several times for minor services in our room - and they were prompt and friendly.Get a room faciling the pool - it's worth the upgrade. The pool is lit up at night with the Strip's light in the background. You can open up your french doors that look over the pool and soak in all of the sights. If you're in the room before the pool closes - you'll get to listen to rock and roll music and enjoy the sun coming in/setting.we were nervous about the reviews regarding the construction. And it was not that big of deal. We could &quot;kind of hear&quot; some typical construction noises in the morning - and we didn't notice anything at the pool They have the great Rock and Roll music playing. So don't worry about the construction. Sometimes you can hear the planes - but it just depends on what their flight paths are during the day. They have a shuttle you can use - and taxis are always usefu. If you have a designated driver, renting a car is a nice option. They have a self park - that is free and VERY convienently located/connected to the main building. It will save you a lot of money in cab fares - IF you have a designated driver.Overall, this is our number one place to stay. We've been here alone with just the two of us, we've brought our children (12 and 13 years), and our grandparents. It's a great setting for all. But if you're 21 to 30 - and like the night scene and young bodies - of course this is even more ideal. But there are all ages here too. And they treat you all the same. You feel valued as a guest - even if you're not 25 and a model's body. Looking forward to coming back and staying in the NEW towers - though the Casino Rooms are classic.We'll be back.	
