Mar 19 2009 	Disappointing	I found a great deal so I was looking forward to staying here, but I found the room and experience disappointing. The bathroom is very small. There was no counter, just a sink. I had nowhere to set my toiletries. I've never seen that in a hotel. The beds are comfy, and there is a large flat screen TV. Room noise is an issue because you are close to the airport so be prepared for jet noise, plus noisy guests walking down the hall in the wee hours, which you can hear right through the door. In a nice touch there are french doors that open to the outside. The room is stocked with overpriced water and snacks. Go to the CVS across the street. No coffee maker either in the room. The casino is filled with restaurants but I found them pricy. Mr Lucky's the diner is the cheapest of the lot but you can pay a lot less for diner food elsewhere. But the wait staff was nice.  The pool area is beautiful and probably the high point of the hotel. There is construction going on around the pool area with two new towers going up, but the noise was not an issue. Again drink prices from the pool bar are pricy. $7 for a can of Heineken. The bartenders and staff are very friendly though.  You will be charged a $7.63 a day resort fee, whatever that is. I just get the feeling this place is nickle and diming you with this mysterious fee and the overpriced goods in your room. I resented that. Finally the place seems isolated with no convenient way to get around if you don't have a car. It's over 2 miles to the strip through some dodgy neighborhoods. There is a free shuttle that runs from 11am to 9pm. It leaves from the front of the Hard Rock Cafe on the corner and drops you off at the Showcase Mall (next to MGM) But if you stay out later (and most of us will) getting back will run you a $10 plus cab ride. That adds up.	
