Jan 6 2009	Wasted Space Nightclub Review	Wasted Space, the Hard Rock Resort Hotel &amp; Casino's new &quot;anti club&quot; nightclub, is not what it is purported to be in its advertising. The only difference between it and every other resort hotel nightclub like Pure, Lavo, Tao,or the Voodoo Lounge is that you can wear street clothes (yes, tennies &amp;t-shirts!) , and its sound system is worse than those in the other clubs. Other than those differences, Wasted Space is just another dark, Hip-Hop/House music club. Yes, there's a little rock, but it's set to a serious hip-hop beat, so it doesn't sound like rock at all. And, with the distorted sound coming from a mediocre system, it's like torture.My suggestion to Carey Hart, Jason Giambi, &amp; Benji and Joel Madden is to be true to your club's advertising. If it's a rock club as you state (“I wanted a place where my friends and I could hang out and listen to some great rock music with a cool atmosphere…there were no options in Vegas, so I made my own,” said Hart), then play rock, and don't change the rock. It's what we rock n' rollers expect when we get there. Also, if you're an &quot;anti-club&quot; unlike the other Vegas clubs, allow your patrons to sit, relax and party to the beat of some real rock drumming without having to spend $200 for a fifth of Grey Goose and a booth. Last but not least, Guys, get a decent sound system.What a disappointment it was for me, a former regular in the mid 90s at the Hard Rock Hotel, to have been so excited to check out the new venue Wasted Space, only to find out that it is truly a waste of space.	
Jan 5 2009 	Fun place to stay	Hard Rock Hotel is a fun off-strip hotel in Las Vegas catered to a hip, young crowd. I am in my mid thirties and I've stayed here on two separate trips to Vegas and have enjoyed it both times. The rooms are clean and modern and the overall vibe can't be beat. The casino is small, but has a nice bar which is a fun place to grab a drink before heading out. The Pink Taco is a great casual mexican restaurant with good, inexpensive food. There is also a 24-hour diner type restaurant that has decent burgers and breakfast.This isn't a luxury property but if you a looking for a fun, hip hotel on a moderate budget, it may be a good choice for you.	
Jan 4 2009	Hard Rock Casino Hollywood Florida	The Hotel is new and very expensive. Don't waste your time or money in this Casino. They use nothing but those cheating pile of crap auto shuffler machines on the lower limit black jack tables. I have gone four times and lost money all four times.They have stacked the odds heavily against you with these auto shufflers. Also keep in mind any time you play the Indians you play a self regulated Casino. Which in my opinion is a huge house advantage. Unlike Vegas, the Indians create and apply their own policy in the casinos. Now who do you think they are looking out for? If you guessed the Indians, you are correct.The slot machines are all controlled my some &quot;Whopperesq&quot; computer system that is probably always working the odds away from you.So in my humble opinion, STAY WAY! Don't cry, I warned you. Go to Vegas, they are giving away rooms now near Freemont, or go on a cruise on NCL, Carnival, or Royal Caribbean instead. You will be able to play hand shuffled shoes in these places where you can almost make 50 - 50 odds against the house.By the way, unlike Vegas, you also get treated to expensive drinks at $7 a pop in the hard rock. So you need to pay for your drinks just so you can give the house an added advantage. That sucks if you ask me..	
Jan 3 2009 	Serves its purpose	Stayed at the hard rock for three nights recently for a guys getaway. Enjoyed the hotel, the price was right and the rooms were fine.This isn't the place I would take my wife for a nice getaway. It's not fancy, it's a bit smoky and has a little bit of the old Las Vegas feel. Pluses. The beds in the rooms were very comfortable, the rooms had french doors which is nice to get some fresh air. Nice big flat screens with lots of channels. Everyone was very friendly, check in, bellboys, dealers. Casual restaurants had great inexpensive food and the table minimums were low. The place is very fun, it has a good vibe, it isn't massive like most hotels on the strip. I'm sure it would be even better when the pool is open. Did not hear any construction at all, however airport is near and sometimes the planes are loud.Negatives. No fan in bathroom (a good thing to have when staying with guys) room is a bit dated with some scuff marks and wear and tear. Smokey gambling floor which is annoying.All in all I would recommend the Hard Rock for a guys getaway or for a fun inexpensive weekend.	
