Nov 14 2008	Fun Place All Young People.	Have gambled and partied at the Hard Rock many times before, but a recent bachelor party wknd gave me the opportunity to finally stay over. Place is definately fun. All weekend long, seemed like 90% of the guests are under 35. At night, everyone dresses sexy, and the casino and lobby area becomes pretty hot. Compared to the other mega-casinos, I liked the small size. PROS Room was pretty good, modern looking, with a very comfy platform bed, a cool light beam in the corner, and a flat screen tv. Had a view of the pool which was great, because all day saturday while lying in bed nursing off a devestating hangover, was fun listening to the pool dj play popular toons through the open doors. CONS Bathroom was small and not very upscale, and the TV didn't wouldn't get to regular channels, just music stations. Called downstairs and tried to explain how to reset it, but that didn't work. They offered to send someone up and comp my intenet (at $14 per 24 hrs) which was nice, but neither actually occured. I was too much in a rush checking out to fight about it. Also, the room while modern designed, is starting to feel a little dated, however the bachelor had a suite, which was newly renovated and looked pretty damn cool. Also the public areas and hallways need a freshening, sounds like this is planned for a year out from now. Have eaten at one the NY branches of Nobu and Ago and the LA branch of Pink Taco, so didn't feel the need to hit these places again. Didn't try the spa. Did order room service breakfast one morning. Came quickly. French toast was warm and delicious, but the smoothie sucked. Clearly was just ice and juice and appeared to have been not freshly made. Also when I came back later that day, the housekeeper moved the trey out to the hallway, but it was still there hours and hours later. All in all, good fun, would def go back for the right price, we paid $99/night. One of my Vegas favorites.	
Nov 12 2008	I Love The Sound Of Construction In The Morning!!!	I LOVE punishment it seems.I knew there was construction going on, but I just didn't think it would be THIS BAD. At around 5:30am, the AIR HORNS go off...yes, I said AIR HORNS. I don't know whose job it is to simply blow an air horn every 10 minutes, but its seems that if I wasn't up until 2 am, that it would be a fun job, and certainly the person in charge of air horn blowing at the massive construction site next to the pool does enjoy his job...thoroughly!Then there are the dump trucks, hammering and the coming together of steel beams. This, if done in the right order, creates an spectacular vibration throughout the hotel...did I mention this was at 5:30am? Just making sure...Oh wait, something serious must be going on...the AIR HORN MAN has now stepped it up to every 5 minutes...My view from my superior King bed room, overlooking the dorment pool (its closed and needs a serious cleaning) allows me a spectacular view of the Venetian, MGM and Paris (who's guests are still sleeping). Now add the gentle rumble of the cement mixer and some Spanish swear words drifting up with the dust clouds at the construction site and you have the cherry on top...PURE HELL! Did I mention this is at 5:45am?This hotel used to be fun, but without the pool, it is GARBAGE! Oh, and did I mention the AIR HORN???Moving to the Palms tonight...this is ridiculous!	
