Sep 30 2008 	No other Vegas hotel compares for us!	Well, again I only have positive things to say about the Hard Rock. My husband and I are in our 30's, don't really drink, and don't stay up late. We STILL have an awesome time every time we come here. The primary reasons for this are: great music, friendly dealers, good comps, comfortable and chic rooms, amenities open at all hours of the day &amp; night, easy to navigate casino, the list is endless!! The construction did not bother us at all... yes you could hear beeps in the morning, but it didn't keep me from sleeping, it was very faint. We had a pool view room and it was so nice! We've only ever had a mountain view here in the past, so this was a real treat. If you sign up for their player's card, you will get offers in your email for comped or really cheap rooms, which is what we did. While there we enjoyed AJ's Steakhouse and the Foo Fighters show at the Joint. Both surpassed expectations. My only critique is that once the construction is done, this perfectly sized hotel will be twice the size, and that makes me sad :( But not sad enough, I will always stay here!	
Sep 25 2008 	A WONDERFUL LITTLE HOTEL IN VEGAS!	The Hard Rock Hotel is the only Vegas hotel we will ever stay at again! Excellent value, spotless room and wonderful location. Yes, we knew the hotel was undergoing construction but tell me what Vegas hotel is not under construction??? They ALL are!!!OK, we are in our 50s and actually I own a small upscale lodging property. So you can imagine that I looked over the hotel room very carefully. We have stayed at other much more expensive and much larger Vegas hotels -- never again!We were overnight guests at the HARD ROCK HOTEL on Sept 21, 08. Oh my -- this hotel is a breeze for parking and for checking in and out. You are not walking for miles and miles inside the hotel to come and go from your room. You can actually ENJOY the hotel -- and the staff are VERY friendly people, and even the store keepers are full of SMILES! We enjoyed the hotel located EXACTLY one mile off &quot;The Strip&quot; from The Bellagio and Caesars.Our room was on the 11th floor. The two king beds were spotlessly WHITE with not one smudge or spot whatsoever on any of the bedding including the waffle weave jacquard duvet -- and the six spotlessly WHITE pillows on each bed. And mind you, the beds were VERY comfortable . The bathroom was absolutely spotless including all grout lines around the tiles on the floor and in the tub/shower. The sink and counter were spotless. I wondered if the entire hotel has just been refurbished because everything -- though modest -- was so fresh and CLEAN!Our room was on the pool side, however the pool and the rock music blaring at the pool close down at 6 in the evening, so nothing to worry about there. We remembered to bring our drinking water with us because as with any Vegas hotel, bottled water requires you to nearly take out a mortgage on your home ($8 - $11/bottle of water).All in all -- a nice little hotel with room rates that don't keep you awake all night. We will definitely stay again. Oh, did I mention that the Hard Rock Hotel is VERY CLEAN (hahaha).P.S. Excellent room air conditioning!!!!!	
