May 1 2008 	Stay away from the Las Vegas Hard Rock Hotel until mid-2009	Stay away from the Hard Rock Hotel in Las Vegas until mid-2009.A $750M renovation began in 2007 immediately adjacent to the existing Hard Rock Hotel and Casino in Las Vegas which will more than double the size of the property and will not be complete until mid-2009. My four night stay in April to May 2008 was accompanied by continuous 24-hour-a-day construction vehicle backup alarms. During one sleepless night from the ubiquitous beeping, I called hotel security and asked someone named John if there wasn’t some sort of a city ordinance or construction noise abatement law that would preclude construction noise after normal business hours. John didn’t know (or care?) and told me he would have a supervisor call right away - never happened. So I called the Las Vegas police department and was told that there are construction noise abatement laws but that the general contractor for the Hard Rock Hotel and Casino renovation had applied for and received a permit for after-hours construction and that there was nothing the police could do.Bottom line - the owners of the Hard Rock Hotel and Casino in Las Vegas are willing to allow 24-hour-a-day construction immediately adjacent to their existing property, have engaged a general contractor with enough the influence with the city of Las Vegas to circumvent construction noise abatement laws, and are currently content to have their guests greatly inconvenienced in the process.Unless and until a credible post from a member of the Hard Rock Hotel and Casino management complete with contact name and information appears in this forum stating that this after-hours problem has been dealt with and resolved, I strongly recommend that no one stay overnight at this hotel until the renovation is finished in mid-2009.	
