Mar 7 2008 	Rock 	The Hard Rock Hotel &amp; Casino is located about a ½ mile or so from the Strip on Paradise Road &amp; Harmon Avenue. We stayed here on business due to the low price ($69 per night) as compared to similar resorts on the strip. Note: there is a lot of construction going on at the outside of the property and it is difficult to come and go by car. Also, the banging starts pretty early (7am). As you can imagine, the entire property is rock &amp; roll based. As you come in through the main entrance, there is a walkway that surrounds the center casino. To the left is the registration; small with only a few check-in stations but this place is about 20% of the size of the larger strip resorts so there was very little wait. The rooms follow the rock &amp; roll theme with classic rock star pictures on the wall. There is an HD TV in the wall, a refrigerator, a small desk, a chaise style lounge chair and a Bose radio. The bed was comfortable and everything was clean. The bathroom was a bit small and felt cramped. Our first room had a non-functioning TV and maintenance was there right away and got us a new room when they could not fix it. Both rooms were facing Paradise Road and the noise from the construction was audible. If you can, get a room on the pool side until the construction is complete.There is a sharp contrast to the restaurants: 2 are casual (Pink Taco – cool atmosphere, so-so Mexican food; Mr. Lucky’s 24/7 – excellent breakfast) to 3 really expensive trendy places (Nobu, Ago &amp; AJ’s were too pricey for us). The club was closed during the week and there was only one non-restaurant bar in the casino. The casino is definitely one of the more fun places to gamble with the rock music blasting. The dealers are great and the bartenders were the best with the comps while playing at the bar. As a matter of fact, all the service personnel were top notch.The pool was closed in early March but looks like a fun place to hang out. This does not rival the larger, strip resorts like Mandalay or Venetian in terms of entertainment and posh, but if you are looking for an inexpensive, fun atmosphere, this is a cool place to stay. Deserves about 3 1/2 stars but needs to get through the construction.	
