Oct 26 2007 	OK stay with a filthy room	The Hard Rock was the last of the &quot;energetic&quot; Vegas properties I had not stayed at before. I've been told by friends what a great place this is...great food...great crowd...great ambience. I guess it was like seeing a blockbuster movie that all the critics raved about...you have to come away disappointed. That was my stay.The good...the ambience was very cool...the whole rock-n-roll thing? I get it. And appropriately so, it's 90% rock...with zero rap or hip-hop that I could see. Thank god.The casino was fine other than the two morons at my blackjack table who insisted on sharing their knowledge of all things with everyone else. Seeing as how they kept losing green and black chips left and right, I guess that knowledge stayed back home in Podunk.Ate at Pink Taco, decent Mexican fare...now to the room. WOW. Ever hear of steam-cleaning and carpet shampoo...or are you just content with a carpet that looks like poo. I refused to take my shoes off unless I was getting into the lumpy uneven mattress to go to sleep. The volume on the TV had a mind of its own and would go from a comfortable level to ear-blasting all of its own volition. Like all rooms, mine opened with a double-door t the outside world. That was nice. But I was on the 3rd floor on the pool side. Just about the worst possible view of the pool area you can imagine.One major positive...this property is not a massive city unto itself like some casinos have become. It was easy to get from one end to the other, out to the pool, out to the parking lot, etc.Next review? Four Seasons Las Vegas next week...	
