May 27 2007 	Fun Time in Vegas	We stayed Thursday through Sunday and had a pool view room on the 7th floor. The room we requested was ready when we checked in at 4:00pm.Overall we had a great time. This is my first time staying here (but have visited during previous visits to Vegas) and what I like best is the festive attitude and everyone is really friendly and up for a good time. Another big plus is the relative small size of the hotel and casino (like other reviewers have commented, it's nice to be able to navigate the hotel without a map).The room was clean and comfortable. We asked for extra towels and they gave us six. All of the staff was very accomodating.We had room service once. It was very prompt and relatively affordable but the portions were HUGE. I could have eaten three meals from one appetizer and entree - I felt guilty throwing so much away. Overall I would say the quality was good but not great.Nobu is in my top five restaurants of all time. If you like Japanese food I can't recommend it highly enough. I also like the Pink Taco but mostly for the vibe and drinks - the food is good but not great.Here is my feedback on some comments from other reviews:I had no issues with noise from the hallway or noise in general.Although technically outside beverages and food are prohibited, we, along with other people I saw, brought these into the hotel without issue.There were glasses and an ice bucket in my room. I thought the water from the faucet had a slight off taste so I went for bottled water which is expensive (until I went across the street and bought my own).The shower water pressure is pretty good but the shower head is a little low for my 6'1&quot; size. This isn't a negative as few shower heads are high enough.The plasma tv is nice and the picture quality was very good.There are a majority of young and fit people at this hotel. However, it's not like the pool is full of models. I saw young and old, skinny and fat, singles and people with children and no one seemed to care one way or another.I had no issues with security and nothing in my room seemed to be disturbed.If you turn the tv on (but don't turn the channel), it plays the same music that plays in the hotel and the pool.It has been a little over a year since I have been to Vegas and I'd have to say that the biggest dissapointment is the attitude of the dealers in the casinos. We visited a number of casinos and found this to be the case everywhere. I'd say the Hard Rock is better than most but it's still worse than the last time I was here (and I had the same thought after my previous visit).	
May 24 2007 	Great pool great atmosphere no complaints	I stayed at the HR May 15-18 with a group of five girls. We were concerned about the $50 per person charge, but we just told them we only had two people in the room. Later, we called guest services and got a rollaway bed. We were only charged for the rollaway ($25 per day) and not for the extra people. The service was great the whole time we were there. We called several times for extra towels and they were brought up immediately.The entire experience was really great. The pool is wonderful and we were able to find chairs at 10 a.m. on each day except it got very busy on Friday. I'm sure that is how it is on weekends. The casino is a smaller scale than those on the strip, which I preferred. We went to the Rock Spa on our last morning, and that was a really relaxing way to end the trip. I recommend eating at Nobu if you like Japanese food -- we had a great meal there. Body English was only open one night while we were there and they closed too early (3 a.m.) for us to make it there.I'd definitely stay there again next time. The only drawback was the distance to the strip, but cabs are always available and only cost about $8 to other casinos.	
