Apr 3 2007 	Great hotel but watch out for sneaky management!	Watch out for Manuel!!My 3 girlfriends and I stayed at The HardRock on March 30- April 1st and it was an overall GREAT hotel. I was a bit skeptical because of some of the reviews I've read on here...... but I will never stay anywhere else in Vegas! Its a few minutes from the strip, but it was a cheap cab ride and not a huge inconvenience at all. Definitely a party hotel, but what else are you going to Vegas for?? I wouldnt recommend it as a family environment......but its classic Vegas and if you are going for a good time, this is definitely the place to go. Unlike some of the other uptight reviews on here, I thought the rooms were wonderful. Decent size for a Vegas room- bigger than several of the rooms I've stayed in in other Vegas hotels. GREAT TV and french door which opened to the pool. We ordered room service the first night and it was delivered pretty quickly.Unbelievable pool atmosphere. We reserved a cabana which was a little pricey, but WELL worth it. We didnt have to fight the crowd for a place to sit and the service was GREAT! Our waitress was Victoria and she was unbelievably nice and helpful. There was a TV, fridge and safe in the cabana, which was nice because you could walk away from your stuff and not have to worry about it getting stolen. It's one big party all day long. Again, I wouldnt recommend it for children. But then again, I don't think most of Vegas is really children-friendly!Now for the downside...... Watch out for some of the hotel management!! I should start out by saying they arent all bad. We were checked out by a very nice man who was courteous, helpful and very respectful. If all management were like him, I would have no complaints. But unfortunately, I can't say the same for the gentleman (and I use that term losely) that checked us in. His name was Manuel (dont know his last name). He was a shorter man with glasses and we were told he was a manager. He came off as very nice and courteous at first.....but dont be fooled!! When we checked in, we were asked how many people we would need wristbands for. Because we were having two people join us at the pool the next day, we listed 4 names. He then had me sign my name on an electronic signature pad for my credit card (the electronic pad did not give me amount though). After giving us the standard speech about the location of the elevators blah blah, he vaguely mentioned something about an extra charge for more people. When I asked him what he was talking about, he said that there was an extra charge for the extra 2 people we listed. We asked him what the charge was and he danced around the question and wouldnt give us a straight answer. Once he realized I wasnt leaving until I got a straight answer, he admitted that there was a $50 extra charge PER PERSON PER NIGHT. I asked him if this charge was in what I had just signed for and he said yes. I found it funny (and very sneaky) that he &quot;forgot&quot; to mention this BEFORE I signed. I pointed out that we only wanted the wristband and there would not be extra people in our room. Manuel then told me that it would be an extra 50 for each wristband anyways (which was a lie!!) I asked him if this was true even if we rented a cabana and he said yes (which was another lie!) Because I could tell he was not going to be up front about anything, I asked for a print out of the charges to my credit card for the room. Manuel told me &quot;we dont do that.&quot; Feeling like he misunderstood what I was asking for, I told him again that I just wanted a copy of my bill to see what the charges were. He again said they didnt do that and that they had no way of printing one. I said again &quot;So you don't give your guests any record of what you charged them?&quot; and his response was &quot;that is correct&quot;. Well anyone who has ever stayed at a hotel before knows that there are printers right at the computer and all hotels will give a guest a copy of their bill! They usually do it without even having to ask!! Needless to say, he was lying. I was able to get a copy of my bill the next day from another person at the front desk. And of course, they printed it from the very computer that Manuel was using when we checked in!! Again, I'm sure all management isnt as dishonest as Manuel, but please be aware!! Require them to give you a copy of the charges at the beginning and end of your stay. And if you get Manuel, ask to check-in with someone else!! He will try to rip you off!!	
