fortunately he was in a meeting but the another agent at the desk asked if she could help us. Luckily for us she was able to call the bank and release the authorization from our debit card. She was the best part of our experience at the Hard Rock. So, we spent the first 2 hours of our time at the Hard Rock trying to check in and settle our bank account. Not a good start.On the day we were to check out we inquired about a late check out. We were told we could extend our check out to 1:00 pm for an additonal $100.00. The Hard Rock doesn't appear to regard customer service as much as their guests do.Outside of these issues our overall view of the Hard Rock is that it is a small casino, very average restaurants, very tight with the beverage service (on the third day we got our first &quot;free&quot; beverage service while gambling), pool area closed and just a lack of customer service. Next year I don't plan on staying here even it my business requires me to be there. Will stay elsewhere and take a cab!	
