Jan 8 2007	We like the Hard Rock!	We went to the Hard Rock with our teenaged girls, and it didn't disappoint. It's not a megaresort like the Bellagio or Venetian and doesn't claim to be a luxury hotel, and as a result is quite a bit cheaper than some others. One can actually see to the other side of the casino and find their way around. I find that refreshing, as I don't like having to find landmarks to find my way back to the elevators in some of the bigger places. All of us enjoyed the rock memorabilia (bow to the shrine to Kurt Cobain) and the constant rock music (in the hallways, the elevator...if you don't want to hear the Stones / Animals/ Nirvana in the background all day, don't stay here). The rooms were as they appeared on the website. I was surprised not to find a coffee maker but everything else was fine. Beds were comfortable, everything was clean. I love a deep bathtub and found it here. We didn't have any trouble with the front desk staff. We ate a couple of times at Mr. Lucky's 24/7, and had reasonably good food for reasonable prices. I had french toast made from a Cinnabon -- my god. I'll go back for that alone.It was too cold to swim, but the pool area looks amazing. We'll probably stay here again in the Spring when things warm up. All in all, we recommend the Hard Rock.	
