Sep 12 2006 	The Hard Rock rocks	Stayed here for 3 nights in early Sep 2006.Great location - 5 mins/$7 in a cab from the airport. Short cab ride or brisk (hot) walk to the strip - walking not recommended.Check-in is probably the only downside - see if you can pre-register or arrive at a quiet time otherwise you have to register, leave your bags and return later (say 5pm) to actually get the keys to your room.Rooms are spacious and clean but room service is late (well after 1pm) and erractic (our beds weren't made and our towels weren't changed one day).The Sunday pool party (rehab) is great fun - well worth being in town for. Pool complex is really good but does get busy so arrive early for a lounger.Casino is OK - min bet $10 though - bar is good and open all hours.Food is good at both the breakfast bar and the other eateries and the starbucks is helpful.All in all great fun: would come again.	
Aug 28 2006 	HR Rocked	I stayed a the HR with my girlfriend in mid August. We are in our late 20's (26,28). We had a great time. The HR treated us well. I have stayed at many other Vegas hotels but none like this. We never felt lost or in a sea of people like other strip hotels. (This hotel Tops THEhotel for overall experience.) Friendliest dealers by far in Vegas. I loved playing cards to good old Rock-N-Roll. Never had more fun playing at the tables. I met lots of good people at the tables. I enjoyed that the casino was much lighter, smaller, and more open than other Vegas Casinos. There were plenty of non-smoking tables open. We really liked the party atmosphere. It was not too much but just right. If you like to play at the tables or the slots I recommend getting a Back Stage Pass (Players Card) before you start gambling. The HR is extremely generous with comps. Most places on the strip do not even let you get a players card unless you play at least $25 a hand. That is not the case at the HR. Once you play for a while just ask the pit boss if you have any comps for food or anything else. They are nice and will tell you yes more than no. Not only that, once you are on that list they will send you special email offers. I just got one that offered rooms as low as $25 in the week and $49 on the weekend!Food at Mr. Lucky's was great. My girlfriend loved the oversized bowl of coffee. Pink Taco was a pleasant surprise. The Guac plate was perfect. The room was good. The carpet was a little wet (from the steam clean) when we checked in, but at least I knew it was clean!! Loved the french doors opening to fresh mountain air. I am glad I brought some CD's for the Bose stereo. I did enjoy the large plasma and the live concert channel was showing Woodstock. The bath tub looked new and was a great excuse to just relax a little.The pool was very nice escape. I will say that we were lucky to get an umbrella. With out that we would have fried.I had a few celeb sightings. Tommy Lee, Dave Navarro, and Wee Man. I missed Mike Tyson on a couple of occasions. Overall I think the HR is the place to be in Vegas. I have already booked another trip in December with a group.	
