Mar 20 2006	Hotel management? Get on the ball...	The Hard Rock Hotel used to be a sanctuary from the strip. Light and breezy rooms, a hipper and more laid back clientele and and a break from the stuffiness afforded by the more mature Strip casinos. However, that has now given way to absolute anarchy on the part of the guests and seeming indifference on behalf of the hotel management. I've stayed here at least a half a dozen times over the past 8 or so years and have seen a slow decline both in the decor (time for a major update guys) and the manner in which the hotel is operated. First, yes, this is a &quot;party&quot; hotel and draws a much younger crowd on average but get some security on the hotel room floors guys. There's no reason, and its unacceptable, that people can host loud parties in their rooms that spill in to the hallways at 4 am. Also, we asked for a non-smoking room only to have pillows that clearly came from a smoking room. We also had zero maid service (we left our room at 9am, came back at 2 pm and then left again at 4 pm ultimately returning past midnight) in our two night stay. I loved the casualness of this hotel but this experience has permanently turned me off from staying here in the future.	
