Jan 17 2006	Great Stay At The Hard Rock!	We have been to Vegas several times and have stayed at a different hotel each time. This visit was a short one night stay as we were only driving through Vegas. The check-in was quick and easy. We got to our room quickly (after parking in their parkade). The pool closed quite early that night (6pm) but I think it might have been slightly earlier than normal because they were doing some sort of re-tiling work on it later in the evening. The restaurants are great! (Mr. Lucky's 24/7 and Pink Taco in the hotel, and the Hard Rock Cafe on site, but not actually in the hotel) and we loved the loud music playing all over the hotel! This hotel is off the strip, so if you have seen and done everything on the strip and want a break from it, this is a great place to stay. It takes about 25 minutes to walk to the strip, or the hotel has a shuttle, or there are always lots of taxis available.The room was awesome! It is a slightly above average sized room for Vegas. We had a room with a pool view. The beds were very comfortable and the Bose stereo, big screen plasma TV, and stocked mini-bar were great extras! It was nice that the shower and toilet were separate from the sink and mirror. The only complaint I would have was that the bathroom floor didn't seem completely clean. There were spots on the tile (what looked like water spots from people getting out of the shower), but it wasn't a big deal as we were only there for a night and I always lay down towels anyway.The pool was the part of the hotel that I was most excited about so we tried it the next morning. It was wonderful! There was plenty of loungers on either sand beach areas or tiled areas. The &quot;sand&quot; however is more like rocks (I guess to keep it at the edges of the pool and not in the filters) and really hurt my feet so I had to keep sandals on when I walked on it. There are waitresses who will bring you drinks and food. The cabanas looked great with chairs, a fan and fridge and music, but we didn't rent one because we were only there for a quick visit. There is one area in the pool that is very shallow, like a lap pool so you can sit in the water to keep cool, but still be in the sun! There is even swim-up blackjack but it wasn't open as early as we were at the pool.This hotel is a great place to stay if you want to be away from the strip in Vegas. If you want a fun hotel with great staff, awesome music, and a lively atmosphere the Hard Rock is for you!	
Jan 4 2006	Fantastic stay at the Hard Rock Hotel in Vegas!!	After reading horrible reviews from a few sites, I was rather disillusioned about booking my stay at the HRH in Las Vegas and was really expecting the worst. Was I mistaken! The HRH from the moment I walked in was a fabulous experience. I had also heard that if you are over 25 you are ignored. Not so! Starting with the doorman that greated me warmly as I walked in and the gentleman at check-in could not have been more polite and accomodating. We got to our room on the 10th floor and were amazed by how spacious and modern our room was (a bargain at $79/night!) There were French doors that opened to let in fresh air and a large plasma tv on the wall that my husband was quite impressed with. The bathroom is small, but aren't most? It was quiet, but I would have to expect that come Spring Break and Summer vacation, it may become a little rowdy. We could not hear the neighbors on either side of us and never heard a door slam or talking in the hallways like you do at some of the larger hotels. The restaurants are fun (Mr. Lucky's, Pink Taco) although service can be a bit slow. Starbucks was a welcome sight in the morning and no lines! The strip is just a short ride away and we parked at Excalibur one day and TI the next, knowing that they are both easy parking lots to access. We went everywhere we wanted to and it was nice to return to the coziness, not to mention fun of the Hard Rock Hotel. While I was playing the slots my last night there, a casino worker offered to get me a frequent player card. She took my ID and was back in less than 10 minutes with my club card. Great service! I prefer the small hotel experience to what the behemoths on the strip have to offer. We have stayed at many in the past that are impersonal and overpriced, not to mention having to walk a mile to get to the outside (MGM, TI). We would gladly stay at HRH again and will recommend to any and all that are planning a visit to Las Vegas.	
