Sep 27 2005	Pool Closes At 4PM	I generally liked the room, the pool and the Hotel public areas which are of a good quality, although being located away from the strip is a negative factor. The clientel is also a nicer younger crowd than in other hotels in Las VegasHowever, ALL the staff are rude and unhelpful. When you ask for the manager they hang up the phone or keep you waiting half an hour. They do not even attempt to solve your problem. Check in is at 5pm whereas check out is at 11am! (why does it take them so much longer to clean the rooms than in Europe?)The pool is rented for Private Parties EVERY evening/night, which means that it effectively closes at 4pm, when staff start to move you all to one end of the pool and then remove all sun beds and generally hassle you so that you leave. This can lead to confrontations between staff and guests that refuse to leave so early!There are hidden charges for everything! A resort charge of $5 /day is automatically added to your bill and it costs more than $20 to use the gym.Guests are secondary citizens in this Hotel as they obviously make more money from the private parties,events and casino and dont really care whether you enjoy your stay or not.One other negative point is the noise from the corridor leading to the bedrooms which can be heard clearly inside your room	
