as very disinterested and not any more pleasant than the first one. Not only is the security staff dreadful, but many of the bartenders and the waitress are also, especially at the pool. Friday afternoon we were in the pool, I asked four different members of the staff if they would get a waitress for us. We probably waited 2 –3 hours when one finally came by. And then she was extremely rude to us once we did order. And it wasn’t just my friend and I that had trouble with the staff, we heard many other guests complain about some of these same issues. In the guest rooms the beds are very comfortable and very nice. But our sink and tub had an awful drainage problem. The tub took probably 30 – 40 minutes to drain. Luckily there were only two of us. It would have been a horrible scene had we had more people staying in the room with us. I would think the Hard Rock would want their staff to provide good service to the guests. I would imagine they would want return guests and them to tell others how wonderful their stay was. I was absolutely amazed at the dreadful treatment my friend and I received during our stay at the Hard Rock Hotel. I sent a letter to Peter Morton at the Hard Rock and I did receive a phone call from one of his Vice President's. We discussed the situation for a few minutes and he offered a complimentary stay. I told him why would I want to do that!!!!! I told him I would discuss his offer with my friend and see what she thought, since it wasn't just my weekend that was ruined. He said, okay, and to call him back. I called back and left him a message. I never heard back from him. I then sent him a letter and still haven't heard back. Horrible service all the way!!!!	
