Jul 7 2005	Great but its for a specific audience	I had a good time at the hard rock. The place is more geared for partying instead of gambling. The table limits are the same as any south strip casino. The food at the 24 hr diner is relatively cheap for its location. I also had steak at their steakhouse restaurant and it was as good as you would get anywhere else. I don't like the menu in the steakhouse b/c you order everything as one item. You order a steak at a certain price, then vegetables at a certain price and then a starch at a certain price. Doesn't make sense to me, they should just have one price for a meal.One thing to be aware of is that the hotel is about .7mi away from MGM Grand (the nearest casino) so if you don't have a car, you will need a cab for every trip. The rooms are very nice with their Bose radio and flat screen TVs. But, you will pay top dollar for a Saturday stay. HR customers are mostly 25-35. If you exceed this age range you will probably look out of place. I'm sure the Hard Rock will take your money, but when I get too old I will probably stay at Manadalay Bay.	
