Jun 21 2005	Take it from a Local!	Take it from me (A Local). After living in Las Vegas for 61/2 years, I have visited my share of Hotel Casino's. Hard Rock Hotel Casino is by far one of the KeWLeST casino's here. This has become a second home to me. I am known by alot of the staff. I have come across some bad apples with attitudes, but never let that effect my opinion of the place in general. The staff in Mr Lucky's are always awesome to me. Scott in particular gave the best service I have ever received. He has no problem making even your typical local feel like a VIP! Kudo's to him. Most of the dealers are friendly, some have had attitudes but dealing with thousands of drunk tourests daily, people spilling drinks on the table, people bending cards, smoking at the table (not all dealers are smokers) well, you get the idea. Anyone can have a bad day. I have seen more guest's that pissed me off then I have dealers. If you really want to have fun, track down a dealer named Bam Bam, this guy is a ------ to sit at a table and play with. Trust me he will make it for a fun experience. He's usually on Crap's or in the peacock lounge (high stakes room). Ok, no I have never spent the night in the any rooms, I will one of these day's. But I have had some dealings with alot of the staff and have always been treated friendly. You will not find a hotel in town that play's better good old Rock and Roll.  I have been to Body English too, and this club is off the hook if you can get in. 7 to 1 girl to boy ratio. A true high class club. OMG! Rehab? Let me tell you this. I just celebrated my 35th Bday there. This was the most OFF THE HOOK pool party I have ever been to. More hot chicks in bikini's then you know what to do with. The service from Chris at the pool was great. Drink's, food, shot's, water, hot chick's, loud music, sun, what else can you ask for? Only one thing though. If you attend Rehab, you will truly need rehab for a few days after. They should change the name because 