Jun 18 2005	Pretty Cool	I just returned from Las Vegas on a a business trip. The Hard Rock is a really cool hotel. Like anything else, it was its pro's and cons's. Pro's: VERY Clean - the elevators are polished down at least once a day. Leather walls and leopard print carpet, funky. The rooms are in great shape, kept clean and fresh looking. The entire hotel is spotless.Security - At night, there is a security guard posted at the elevators checking roomkeys. no room key - no elevator.The music rocks. It is just awesome to hear classic rock everywehere you go in the hotel. The pool........the whole beach club area is amazing. From the sandy beach that extends right into the pool, to the swimup bar and blackjack tables........it is a great place to hang out.The BOSE alarm clock in the room was spectacular. 102.7 is an all 80's radio station and to have that music on that clock radio every morning was a great way to wake up.The entire staff was tremendously upbeat and accomondating.The Pink Taco has some of the best Mexican food I have ever had. The bed was big and the pillows very SOOOO comfortable.CONS:Booked my room via the web and got a great rate, however my room faced the airport. I was told it was a mountain view room, which it was; the mountains were behind the airport. Extra charges for EVERYTHING. Room Servie adds a $3.00 delivery charge per order. HELLO ??? IT'S ROOM SERVICE. In addition, there is an automatic 18% gratuity added to the bill. Your $9.95 breakfast quickly turns into $14.The mini bar is on a sensor. If you move anything around, you will be charged. Also, upon arrival, I had an iced tea from the mini bar and someone was at my door within 15 minutes to re-stock. Kind of freaky knowing your room is being somewhat monitored.I purchased a sixpack of beer to have in my room. I expected the ice bucket to be filled when i came home back from work that day, but it was not. I assume they are not going to assist you in drinking for cheap at this property.The hotel is not on the strip and the complimentary shuttle stops running at 7pm. you will have to pay for taxi's to get back and forth, it is a pretty good walk from the Hard Rock to Las Vegas blvd.The pool is only open from 9am thru 7pm. So, if you are there for business, you are not going to be able to take a swm at night and enjoy this awesome spot in the hotel. There is a $5.00 per night resort fee added to the room that is supposed to cover the shuttle and pool area. But, again, both shutdown really early.The casino is small in comparison to other hotels in Vegas. Overall, I am glad I got to experience this resort. If you are with a group and don't mind splitting taxi's every night, I would recommend this hotel as a great party place to hang with your friends. Just be prepared to spend your precious gambling $$$$ on TONS of miscellaneous fees.	
