king to book a bachelor party in Vegas, don't look anywhere else!! &lt;p&gt;However, if you're looking to go somewhere in Vegas with your family and kids, or if you're part of an older crowd (my group was late 20's and early 30's), I'd advise you to stay somewhere else. After I get married and I take my family to Vegas, we're sure as heck NOT gonna stay at the Hard Rock. But if you're in my situation, this place cannot be beaten.	
