May 18 2005	Better than anticipated	My hubby, myself and another couple stayed at HRH from 5/15/05 to 5/18/05. We had standard rooms that we had gotten through Expedia for $95/nt. The room was better than I expected. The decor was contemporary in furniture style and the colors neutral. The bed was very comfortable and the feather pillows were heavenly. The plasma screen TV gave and excellent picture. Housekeeping did a great job of cleaning our room early in the day and responded quickly when asked for more towels. The bathroom was average w/ the shower head being very low so that my 6'2&quot; hubby had to duck to get under it. It was also a very deep tub and you have to be careful getting in and out if it. The worst thing about the room was the bathroom lighting. It is horrible. It was nearly impossible to put on makeup. I had to put my face right up to the mirror under the small light and even then I couldn't see. I called to see if they had light up makeup mirrors and was told that they did not. My friend also noted that she had a horrible time seeing in the bathroom too. Definitely could use some updated bathroom lighting.The casino was very nice. We were pleasantly surprised. It is small and round. But even better, they had a lot of $5 min. tables which we were thrilled about as they are hard to find at most places. The piped in music was a much better alternative to annoying slot bells and whistles. The music had a lot of variety in the casino and at the pool. The dealers are very nice and made the gambling experience much more fun.The pool is really nothing great. I did not care for the sand beach part. The water temp was great and bar service at the pool was fast and efficient. The loungers were adequate and the pool towels were nice and big.We are in our early 40's and were led to beleive that we would feel out of place here. We did not. In fact we were about the average age of people staying and gambling there. We enjoyed our stay immensely and would definitely stay again. Next time however we will use the hotel shuttle to get to the strip. Registration neglected to tell us about this perk and we paid a lot of money for taxis.	
