Mar 22 2005	great hotel	My husband and I stayed the the Hard Rock February 22-24, 2005. I must say I fell in love with the hotel as soon as I walked in. The Rock &amp; Roll atmosphere is fabulous and I loved the music. The front desk staff was very pleasant and accommodating. The room was very spacious and beds were very comfortable. There was alot of noise from the airport traffic, however, it didn't bother us in the least. If you are a light sleeper, you will want to request ear plugs. I do wish there was coffee in the room, but it wasn't a big deal. We rented a car this time, so we didn't try the shuttle to the Strip. When we wanted to go to the Strip, we drove &amp; parked at Ballys.The only complaint I have about the Hard Rock is the concierge desk. Being a travel agent, I make sure when I am traveling, I take notice of how I and others are treated by everyone at the hotel. When we went to the concierge desk to ask a question, the gentleman was on the phone. He made no attempt to acknowledge us the entire time we stood in front of his desk. We stood in front of him about 5 minutes until finally giving up. This will be something I will mention to my clients when recommending this hotel.	
