Oct 19 2004	Brilliant atmosphere	Compared to the other large hotels on the strip (such as MGM which are just to big!!) the Hard Rock is an ideal size, you don’t need to have a map just to find your way back to your room!! It was very busy on the weekends, the swimming pool area was jam packed, especial on Sunday when they have their “rehab beach party”, but the rest of the week it was quiet. It was a bit of a drawback that we were set so far back off of the strip (about a 20 min walk), but taxis were only a couple of dollars and there is a free bus which runs till 7pm; and we did have an amazing view from our room (on the 10th floor), which was of the entire length of The Strip; especially amazing at night.	
