Apr 5 2004 	If you love cigarette smoke Las Vegas is for you	The hotel is fine for Las Vegas standards, which assumes that cigarette smoking everywhere doesn't bother you. Las Vegas is one big discarded cigarette butt. Smoking is allowed and encouraged everywhere. Casinos, restaurants, taxis, shuttles, malls, bathrooms. It even smells like stale smoke in the nonsmoking rooms, which we had. The room was a standard view (not of pool or strip) for $315 a night. The bathroom was small with one sink, and the grab bars on the tub are placed such that you whack your shin easily getting in and out of the shower. The lighting in the bathroom is terrible. Also, the water pressure in the shower is nonexistent. The towels are tiny and they only give you two per room. The room is decorated with puke green carpet and purple curtains. The bed was comfortable. The hotel is about a mile from the &quot;strip&quot;. I can't believe that Las Vegas promotes itself as a family destination. It is better known as Sin City. No liquor restrictions and legalized prostitution make the omnipresent gambling seem tame. I've never been in dirtier american city: trash everywhere, including everpresent cigarette butts, discarded beer cans, and millions of naked women phone sex pictures. As you walk along Las Vegas Blvd, there are people pushing the phone sex pictures in your face every five feet, even if you are a child. The taxicabs were the filthiest I've ever seen. We had to go there on business, and will never return for pleasure. What is the attraction with this place?????	
