Mar 9 2004	The Pink Taco	The Pink Taco in the the Hard Rock Hotel is perhaps my favorite restaurant in Vegas. If you love Mexican food....you will love this place. During the week they have a great happy hour from 5-7. Tables in the casino (which are right nearby) have 1 and 3 dollar play limits. Prices are wonderful. Ambience is laid back. This place has served many stars. Ask your server, they are sure to fill your head with a tale or 2 of their star contacts. Hard Rock has a great shop in the same area. Great if you need to pick up a thing or 2 for the kids that are waiting at home for you. If you happen to be with the kids (which we have been) they love to waste and hour or more looking around. THey also love the food at Pink Taco.	
Feb 5 2004	Fantastic way to let your hair down	If your looking for some excitement there is no better way to spend a few days in Vegas than at the HardRock. If your a geezer than stay with Ceaser. Service was great, rooms were nice and clean everything was easily accessible ( not too big). I recommend pool season strongly. I think most poor reviews come from people looking for a quiet getaway.....you picked the wrong spot dad. Dealers and boss's were very nice, not too up tight. Prices are very reasonable and again I can't say enough about the pool. The crowd was young and in great spirits. I'm Booked for May &quot;04&quot; and we'll see if I didn't just catch a good week last year.Keep up the good work	
Jan 14 2004	Did you lose control !	I was there on saterday 1-10-2004. I would like to now what happen that evening that the crowd was diffrent then any other time, gangs, tention, and worst of all people sitting on very nice cars in your casino front door area drinking bottels of nice booze, loud music. it reminded me of a free consert at a park in the getto, people din't get a long that nite. you at the hardrock casino don't like that kind of stuff! you like everyone to have a good good time. I did not, Plaese take care of the poblem.	
Jan 6 2004	New Year's	Hard Rock has large spacious rooms that are decorated in a hip and fun style. The hotel is clean and small enough that it is easy to navigate. Had some noise issues from street but it was New Years so what can you do. Casino is small and cozy with a good vibe. Employee's very friendly. Getting drinks was average. Usually got asked, but slow as any casino. Had Amstel and Heineken bottles on the free list. One time I was out of small bills and I found out no tip and you'll never see a waitress again. Low limit was $10 during day and $15 to 25 at night. Blackjack hits soft 17. Single deck 21 offered with modified rules (surrender, 2:1 blackjack etc). Craps low limit was always at least $10, keeping me off the table. No poker rooms.Pool was closed but looked magnificent. In general crowd was young and beautiful. If you are not, you will probably not get much attention.....Still, the eye candy is worth it! Man or woman, It would take you 3 hours to find half a dozen people you didn't think were gorgeous to look at.Mr Lucky's diner pretty good food at okay price (for a casino) but service was average at best. AJ's was excellent but very expensive. The scallops appetizer was not good. The steak was amazing. Pink Taco - pretty good and moderate price. Hot salsa delicious. Try the salmon.One annoying thing, Casino and Pink Taco share one bathroom location! Crazy.Walk to strip is about a mile of uninteresting but seemingly safe sidewalk. Harmon is busy so cross at lights. Hotel has room service but no room service menu in sight. Also, we tipped maid second to last day and the next day we had horrible maid service (it was a good tip I swear!). No iron. They do have hairdryer. Mirror on head board is curious. I'm sure it is for something kinky but there's only one position you could use it from......I guess that's why they call it the hard rock.	
Jan 1 2004	Good time but resort fee is ridiculous	We stayed over X-Mas (2004) for 3 days at the Hard Rock Hotel. Had a great time. Comfy rooms and rates - at that time - were reasonable ($68). The guy at the check in gave us a room with a nice view towards The Strip. The pool area is closed during the winter time (which was a disappointment; only one small hot tub open). They still wanted to charge us the ridiculous $5 per day resort fee which we refused to pay. This is really one of the most annoying things. You can't use the gym (extra. $18), you can't use the pool and they still want to charge you a resort fee. I told them that this is just a rip off on every customer. Either include it in your hotel room rate or leave it.	
Dec 29 2003	Hit or Miss at the Hard Rock	The experience one has at the Hard Rock has a great deal to do with how busy they are. The one time I stayed at the hotel was during the week leading up to Christmas. This is the slowest season in Las Vegas, and I had mostly very good service at Hard Rock. Check in, restaurant service, room service, and maid service were all totally satisfactory. My time in the casino was also quite good with friendly dealers, pit bosses, and cocktail waitresses. I have had TERRIBLE experiences in the casino at other times I've played there, though. If you like to actually gamble, I suggest you avoid this place like the PLAGUE on Friday and Saturday nights! It is unbelievably noisy, dark, smoky, and FILLED with drunks who are way too busy ogling the girls than to play cards. Sometimes, the dealers get into the ogling as well. I don't care how much cleavage is bouncing by, it STILL shouldn't take 10 minutes to play one hand of blackjack! I also want to point out that I HATE the fact that the $25 chips at the Hard Rock are purple rather than green (which is standard). In the dim lighting, it is far too easy to mistake the $25 chips with the red $5 chips. I learned this the hard way when I accidentally bet two $25 chips when I meant to bet two $5 chips! Incidentally, I drew a 20 on that hand and STILL lost! Very disappointing... Still, the Hard Rock is a very nice place to stay AND gamble if you make sure to do it mid-week or during the daytime. From now on, if I'm staying there, I'll just head over to the strip to gamble at night. Aladdin is just down the street...	
Dec 20 2003	Fun even with kids....	Stayed here in August 2002 for my 30th birthday..Grandparents were all out of town so we had to take the kids, then 6 and 20 mos.Check in was slow, but the staff was nice. When they saw that it was my birthday, the gave me one of thier elusive &quot;funbooks&quot; and upgraded me to a pool/strip view.The rooms are very nice and mod. The hallways are lined with these annoying cymbals that everyone likes to hit! Surprisingly, we slept well both nights. It wasn't rowdy, even though there was some after party several doors down that security broke up..anyways..The pool was fantastic. We hit the pool early and we were one of the few people there. No one gets up before noon at this hotel! We got our beers in cool &quot;tiki&quot; cups that we got to keep.The food places were just average. We had breakfast at the cafe..just blah..didn't go to the other places, too over priced!I would comeback and stay, but with no kids, that's what the Flamingo is for!	
Dec 3 2003	anothe r user commented this hotel is so 80's maybe he should put his flock of seagulls c.d. back in	Whats this person talking about ( Hard Rock Hotel so 80's )Room was decorated very hip, clean and comfy-pay a little extra and request pool side room- balconies although you cant actually walk outto them french doors opened up to get a nuiice brezze in and for you to enjoy sounds and sights- speaking of sights thier is plenty at the pool and the pool is top notch sand bottom- music underwater etc.Staff needed some help with manners but besides that hotel is the only place ( minus Bellagio) to be at.So dust of the Depeche Mode and Duran Duran and hit the Rock	
Nov 21 2003	My Favorite Hotel In Vegas!	Next month will be the third time I have stayed in the Hard Rock Hotel in Vegas, and it is absolutely my favorite hotel in Vegas. It is a small hotel by Vegas standards, with no shopping mall or elaborate casino, and has a very cozy feel. The pool is one of the best in Vegas, and the restaurants are unbelievable. The rooms are comfy and posh, as are the black leather and leopard fur elevators and casino. It's an especially great hotel if you have tickets to see a concert at The Joint, the best rock venue in America.	
Nov 14 2003	Fabulous	I was scared after reading bad reviews of the Hard Rock before going there last July. The pool was incredible. Service was great. Food at 24/7 was good and reasonable. I had a positive experience and would return. It is off the stripe so I would only stay there when weather is warm for pool use. Love Las Vegas.	
Oct 16 2003	Hard rock - Rocks!	Great Casino- great rooms- very clean and roomy. I was there with a couple of Navy buds I haven't partied with in years- the Hard Rock did us up right. + if your into it there is a strip joint right across the street- (Club Paradise) talk about ideal location.Only downside no Buffet.- If your 20-30ish and like to party this is the place for you to go!	
Sep 28 2003	Buyer Beware...	Beware of this place and its hidden charges. The place attempts to nickel and dime you at every turn. You won't find this out until checkout though when you view your bill. The room is nice eventhough parts of it are falling apart. Lots of young people but mostly guys...hint....The scene has shifted to the Palms. The Hard Rock is so 90's. LOL Needless to say I won't be staying there again.	
Aug 25 2003	Cool hotel lukewarm staff	Just returned from 3 nights there. We arrived on Monday at 12:30 am and were told that the hotel had oversold the rooms. Even though we had prepaid, there were no rooms available. A very nasty man at check in told us that we could go across the street &quot;on them&quot; to Alexis Park and come back tomorrow. After complaining, a room mysteriously opened up but we had to wait 1 hour for it to be ready. We were very tired still being on east coast time. But the bed was super comfortable, great mattress, and worth the wait. Man at check in was very unconcerned and did not offer us any compensation while we waited. The pool is fantastic, much better than other hotels in Vegas but staff came around and made everyone keep their chairs in single file &quot;fire code&quot; so you could not follow the sun if you were tanning. At check out we were told that there was a 5$ per day &quot;resort fee&quot; which was not included in the price of the room. I don't know what this was actually for. We refused to pay for the first night since we did not even get there until 12:30. Aside from these complaints which were totally related to the staff, the hotel itself is great. We had a pool view and the french doors actually open so you can lean out over pool. The crowd was cool and another plus, hardly any children. I would stay there again but I am now a little wiser about the staff.	
Aug 9 2003	Hopefully It Gets Better	Okay, so I've read all the negative reviews about Hard Rock and ignored them all. I hope I don't regret it. We have booked the rooms for mid next week and I'm already having an issue with the employees. I wanted to book a cabana at the pool on saturday and heard you must call right when they open (9AM) which is 10AM Colorado time. So I did and was told by Jennifer that there was already 5 people on hold. I asked if I could just go ahead and hold. So I did. Had the friends I'm going to Vegas with call also. I was on hold for 5 minutes, she called, got through and was told they were already booked! I, of course was still on hold. The moral of the story, believe what you read.	
Jul 21 2003	Great Pool	Overall we enjoyed our one night stay at the Hard Rock Hotel. The only problem we had is that they would not let us check into our room until 3:00. We arrived at noon and fortunately they gave us wrist bands so we could go out to the pool, which is one of the highlights of the hotel. We attended a concert at The Joint that night which was great as well. The Joint is a great place to see a show. Overall it was a great place to stay except for not being able to check in before 3:00.	
Jul 15 2003	Wonderful Rooms!	The best rooms ever in terms of comfort. The beds are plush; better than those at the W hotels. Din't want to get out of the bed all day and night! Probably not a good thing for the casino, but an excellent place to relax. Quite a suprise.	
Jul 14 2003	Fantastic	I almost cancelled my reservations for the Hard Rock this past June after reading negative reviews such as those posted on this board. I'm sure glad I didn't cause my experience was exactly opposite to that of the naysayers. We're 43, 45 and 54 yrs. old and I dare say we had as good a time, if not better, than any 20-30 yr. olds there. We stayed there Thursday - Sunday and didn't have 1 bad experience. We got there at 8am so our room wasn't ready - no problem - checked our bags with the valet, changed into our suits and had a great time at the pool for the day. By 3pm our room was ready. We simply asked nicely and they upgraded our room to a pool view no problem. All the staff was very friendly, including bar staff. After 3 days quite a few knew our names by heart. If you're friendly to them you'll get it right back, if you act like you expect to get your *** kissed, don't expect much in return. Tables are good, several $5 tables for the minimum betters. Good odds on the craps tables, not just double like some have said. Only ate at the Sushi rest., which was great. Don't bring the kids and expect a party, you'll have a blast. Not that it matters but hanging by the pool and gambling with the likes of Pauly Shore, 50 cent, and the remaining members of The Grateful Dead was pretty cool too.	
Jul 14 2003	Best summer vacation!	I was really surprised how wonderful my stay at Hard Rock was! The Pool of course was awesome, and the young crowd was both tempting and tame! I can't say enough about the quality of the rooms as well...both simple and clean as well as elegant! It's not a problem getting to the strip either with the shuttle running on the hour. All in all, the Hard Rock will be seeing me again as a future visitor!	
Jun 6 2003	If you love pretty women....	Like the title says, if you love pretty women, this is the place to go. I read the reviews about the lousy service, I had no problem. The pure density of sexy, fine women at this place, was tremendous. Going to the strip during the day was pointless, its all about the pool at the hotel. I was there on Monday and Tuesday, and still was impressed with the chicks. Just wish I could have stayed longer.	
